data.value:
Invite your partner to Xena!


Your partner will be able to:

  • - View the invoices you have sent.
  • - View statement of account.
  • - View the documents you have shared.
  • - Write to you.
  • - Pay bills (requires an agreement with DIBS).

You will be able to:
  • - Share documents.
  • - Have your partner maintain contact information.
  • - Communicate with your partner.

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Body_Two
data.value:
You import the complete set of data into the Archive, but you only link and create the data that you need.

See the guide in Xenapedia on how to use the archive.

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Header_One
data.value: Xena Archive - an easy and seamless transition to Xena!

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Article_Groups
data.value:
Create article groups in Xena according to your line of business.

Since article groups are used for both turnover, consumption and stock - it is not necessary to create groups for each. Also, VAT is handled across countries on the same article group.

Sample article groups in Xena could be:

• Services

• Licenses

• Freight

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Accounts
data.value:
Link each account to the most suitable ledger account

It is possible to create your entire general ledger from here, but it is not mandatory. As long as a suitable ledger account is linked, Xena will suggest creation of the accounts you need from the archive.

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Article
data.value:
Create articles in Xena

Firstly, you should link the imported article groups (if any). Hereafter, you can create each article as needed. If you have a lot of articles, you can use the function "Import all articles" on each article group instead.

While it is possible to create all articles from this view, you can also create articles 'on-the-fly' by typing the article number from the imported articles on e.g. the order lines. Xena will then suggest the creation of a linked article according to the information imported.

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_Partner
data.value:
A "Partner" in Xena is all your collaborators - ie. customers, suppliers and employees

From here you can import each partner into Xena.

While it is possible to create all partners from this view, you can also create partners 'on-the-fly' by typing the contact number or telephone number from the imported partners on e.g. the order. Xena will then suggest the creation of a linked partner according to the information imported.

data.name: Views_Archive_Index_Explanation_DataImport
data.value:
How to create data from the archive:

Below, you can create data from the imported archive by going into edit mode (Use the icon or the context menu).

The most important step is to link the article groups and assign the correct ledger account to each account.

While you can create data directly from this view, it is not mandatory. When you enter an account number, telephonenumber or articlenumber, respectively - Xena will suggest a creation dialog based on the imported account.

An API-key in Xena is a user that does not have a person connected to it, as appose to the standard user.
The API-key can be used to gain access to the Xena API for e.g. a webshop, or it can be used to create an item for time tracking, such as a meeting room or a rental car.
